always call 110 and report the scam. if this fails, you should at least ask for a "fapiao" (发票), an official sales invoice issued by the taxation department. it is against the law for an owner to refuse to give it to you. if you have the receipt, you can use it as evidence when making a report later. if you have already been a victim, go back to the shop with more tourists, demand a refund and threaten to call the police. if you paid by credit card, try to negotiate with your bank for a refund. however, high 